        "build_to_last_NUPDV8": {
          "type": "build-to-last",
          "settings": {
            "custom_class": "hc-briefing-designed",
            "eyebrow_text": "02 — RESISTS WEAR AND BREAKDOWN",
            "title": "DESIGNED FOR LONGEVITY",
            "description": "Frequent washing doesn’t just waste resources - it’s also what destroys clothing. Heat, friction, and detergents break down fibers, causing stretching, sagging, and pilling.\n\nBecause HercLéon garments require far less washing, they avoid much of this damage. Combined with a resilient fiber structure engineered to resist wear, they maintain their shape and performance through repeated use. Longer-lasting garments mean fewer replacements, resulting in less textile waste and reduced landfill contribution.",
